---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Arbitrage Calculator"
  description="Use this free arbitrage calculator to check whether betting odds create an underround, calculate stake split, equalised return and possible arbitrage profit."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Betting calculator</p>
    <h1>Arbitrage Calculator</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Use this arbitrage calculator to check whether a set of odds creates an underround and calculate how to split your stake across all outcomes.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Quick explanation:</strong> Arbitrage is possible in theory when the combined implied probability of all outcomes is below 100%. In practice, odds can move, limits can apply and commission can affect the result.
    </div>

    <div class="calculator-panel">
      <div class="calculator-header">
        <div>
          <h2>Enter your stake and odds</h2>
          <p>Add every possible outcome in the market, then enter the odds available for each one.</p>
        </div>
        <button class="button secondary small-button" type="button" id="reset-arb">Reset example</button>
      </div>

      <label class="stake-box">
        <span>Total stake</span>
        <div class="stake-input-wrap">
          <span>£</span>
          <input id="total-stake" type="number" min="0.01" step="0.01" value="100" />
        </div>
        <small>The total amount to split across all outcomes.</small>
      </label>

      <div class="market-table-wrap">
        <table class="market-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Outcome</th>
              <th>Decimal odds</th>
              <th>Implied probability</th>
              <th>Stake</th>
              <th></th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="arb-rows">
            <tr>
              <td><input type="text" value="Outcome A" aria-label="Outcome name" /></td>
              <td><input type="number" value="2.10" min="1.01" step="0.01" aria-label="Decimal odds" /></td>
              <td class="probability-cell">47.62%</td>
              <td class="stake-cell">£50.00</td>
              <td><button class="remove-row" type="button" aria-label="Remove outcome">×</button></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><input type="text" value="Outcome B" aria-label="Outcome name" /></td>
              <td><input type="number" value="2.10" min="1.01" step="0.01" aria-label="Decimal odds" /></td>
              <td class="probability-cell">47.62%</td>
              <td class="stake-cell">£50.00</td>
              <td><button class="remove-row" type="button" aria-label="Remove outcome">×</button></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="calculator-actions">
        <button class="button primary" type="button" id="add-outcome">Add outcome</button>
      </div>

      <div class="results-grid">
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>Book percentage</span>
          <strong id="book-result">95.24%</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>Underround / overround</span>
          <strong id="margin-result">4.76% underround</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>Equal return</span>
          <strong id="return-result">£105.00</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card">
          <span>Estimated profit</span>
          <strong id="profit-result">£5.00</strong>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="result-note" id="result-note">
        This example creates an underround. Splitting £100.00 across all outcomes would return about £105.00, giving an estimated profit of £5.00.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>What is arbitrage betting?</h2>
    <p>
      Arbitrage betting is when the available odds allow every possible outcome in a market to be covered for a profit. This usually happens when prices across different bookmakers or exchanges create an underround.
    </p>
    <p>
      The maths can look simple, but real-world execution is harder. Odds can move, bets can be limited, markets can suspend and exchange commission can reduce or remove the profit.
    </p>

    <h2>Arbitrage formula</h2>
    <div class="formula-box">
      <p><strong>Implied probability</strong> = 1 ÷ decimal odds × 100</p>
      <p><strong>Book percentage</strong> = all implied probabilities added together</p>
      <p><strong>Arbitrage exists in theory</strong> when book percentage is below 100%</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Arbitrage example</h2>
    <p>
      If Outcome A is available at 2.10 and Outcome B is also available at 2.10, each outcome has an implied probability of 47.62%.
    </p>

    <table class="example-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Outcome</th>
          <th>Decimal odds</th>
          <th>Implied probability</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Outcome A</td>
          <td>2.10</td>
          <td>47.62%</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Outcome B</td>
          <td>2.10</td>
          <td>47.62%</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="formula-box">
      <p>47.62% + 47.62% = 95.24%</p>
    </div>

    <p>
      Because the total is below 100%, this is an underround. In theory, that allows both outcomes to be covered for a profit.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Why arbitrage can be difficult in practice</h2>
    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Odds can move before all bets are placed.</li>
      <li>Stake limits can prevent the correct stake split.</li>
      <li>Markets can suspend before the second bet is placed.</li>
      <li>Bookmakers may have different settlement rules.</li>
      <li>Exchange commission can reduce the profit.</li>
      <li>Account restrictions can affect repeat use.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Important:</strong> An arbitrage calculator can show the maths, but it cannot guarantee that all bets can be placed at the required odds.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Related tools</h2>
    <div class="related-grid">
      <a class="related-card" href="/calculators/overround-calculator/">
        <h3>Overround Calculator</h3>
        <p>Check whether a market is overround or underround.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="related-card" href="/calculators/dutching-calculator/">
        <h3>Dutching Calculator</h3>
        <p>Split a stake across selected outcomes.</p>
      </a>
      <a class="related-card" href="/guides/dutching-vs-arbitrage/">
        <h3>Dutching vs Arbitrage</h3>
        <p>Learn the difference between stake splitting and arbitrage.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .calculator-panel {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      background: #ffffff;
    }

    .calculator-header {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .calculator-header h2 {
      margin: 0;
    }

    .calculator-header p {
      margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .small-button {
      padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .stake-box {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
      max-width: 360px;
    }

    .stake-box > span {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .stake-input-wrap {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      background: white;
    }

    .stake-input-wrap span {
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .stake-input-wrap input {
      width: 100%;
      border: 0;
      padding: 0.5rem 0;
      font: inherit;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--color-text);
      background: transparent;
    }

    .stake-input-wrap input:focus {
      outline: 0;
    }

    .stake-box small {
      display: block;
      margin-top: 0.45rem;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .market-table-wrap {
      overflow-x: auto;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
    }

    .market-table,
    .example-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      background: white;
    }

    .market-table th,
    .market-table td,
    .example-table th,
    .example-table td {
      padding: 0.75rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      text-align: left;
      vertical-align: middle;
    }

    .market-table th,
    .example-table th {
      color: var(--color-navy);
      background: #f4f7fa;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .market-table input {
      width: 100%;
      min-width: 110px;
      padding: 0.65rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      color: var(--color-text);
      font: inherit;
    }

    .probability-cell,
    .stake-cell {
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

    .remove-row {
      display: inline-grid;
      place-items: center;
      width: 34px;
      height: 34px;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: white;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .remove-row:hover {
      color: #b42318;
      border-color: #f3b7b2;
      background: #fff1f0;
    }

    .calculator-actions {
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .results-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .result-card {
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .result-card span {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
      color: var(--color-muted);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
    }

    .result-card strong {
      display: block;
      color: var(--color-navy);
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      line-height: 1.2;
    }

    .result-card strong.positive {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
    }

    .result-card strong.negative {
      color: #b42318;
    }

    .result-note {
      margin: 1rem 0 0;
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 12px;
      background: #eef8f3;
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .result-note.warning {
      background: #fff7e6;
      color: #8a5a00;
    }

    .result-note.error {
      background: #fff1f0;
      color: #b42318;
    }

    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .formula-box {
      padding: 1rem 1.15rem;
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .formula-box p {
      margin: 0.4rem 0;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .standard-list {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
    }

    .standard-list li {
      margin: 0.45rem 0;
    }

    .related-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }

    .related-card {
      display: block;
      padding: 1rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      border-radius: 14px;
      background: var(--color-bg);
    }

    .related-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(31, 138, 91, 0.45);
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }

    .related-card p {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--color-muted);
    }

    .callout a,
    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px) {
      .results-grid,
      .related-grid {
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .calculator-header {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .results-grid,
      .related-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    const tableBody = document.getElementById("arb-rows");
    const totalStakeInput = document.getElementById("total-stake");
    const addButton = document.getElementById("add-outcome");
    const resetButton = document.getElementById("reset-arb");

    const bookResult = document.getElementById("book-result");
    const marginResult = document.getElementById("margin-result");
    const returnResult = document.getElementById("return-result");
    const profitResult = document.getElementById("profit-result");
    const resultNote = document.getElementById("result-note");

    const exampleRows = [
      { name: "Outcome A", odds: "2.10" },
      { name: "Outcome B", odds: "2.10" }
    ];

    function formatMoney(value) {
      return new Intl.NumberFormat("en-GB", {
        style: "currency",
        currency: "GBP",
        minimumFractionDigits: 2,
        maximumFractionDigits: 2
      }).format(value);
    }

    function formatPercent(value) {
      return `${value.toFixed(2)}%`;
    }

    function createRow(name = "Outcome", odds = "") {
      const row = document.createElement("tr");
      row.innerHTML = `
        <td><input type="text" value="${name}" aria-label="Outcome name" /></td>
        <td><input type="number" value="${odds}" min="1.01" step="0.01" aria-label="Decimal odds" /></td>
        <td class="probability-cell">—</td>
        <td class="stake-cell">—</td>
        <td><button class="remove-row" type="button" aria-label="Remove outcome">×</button></td>
      `;
      return row;
    }

    function setError(message) {
      bookResult.textContent = "—";
      marginResult.textContent = "—";
      returnResult.textContent = "—";
      profitResult.textContent = "—";
      profitResult.className = "";
      resultNote.textContent = message;
      resultNote.className = "result-note error";

      tableBody.querySelectorAll("tr").forEach((row) => {
        row.querySelector(".probability-cell").textContent = "—";
        row.querySelector(".stake-cell").textContent = "—";
      });
    }

    function calculateArbitrage() {
      const totalStake = Number(totalStakeInput.value);
      const rows = Array.from(tableBody.querySelectorAll("tr"));

      if (!Number.isFinite(totalStake) || totalStake <= 0) {
        setError("Please enter a total stake greater than £0.");
        return;
      }

      let impliedSum = 0;
      let hasInvalidOdds = false;
      const outcomes = [];

      rows.forEach((row) => {
        const oddsInput = row.querySelector('input[type="number"]');
        const probabilityCell = row.querySelector(".probability-cell");
        const odds = Number(oddsInput.value);

        if (!oddsInput.value || !Number.isFinite(odds) || odds <= 1) {
          probabilityCell.textContent = "Invalid";
          hasInvalidOdds = true;
          return;
        }

        const implied = 1 / odds;
        impliedSum += implied;
        outcomes.push({ row, odds, implied });
        probabilityCell.textContent = formatPercent(implied * 100);
      });

      if (hasInvalidOdds || outcomes.length < 2) {
        setError("Please enter valid decimal odds greater than 1.00 for at least two outcomes.");
        return;
      }

      const equalReturn = totalStake / impliedSum;
      const profit = equalReturn - totalStake;
      const bookPercentage = impliedSum * 100;
      const margin = Math.abs(bookPercentage - 100);

      outcomes.forEach((outcome) => {
        const stake = equalReturn / outcome.odds;
        outcome.row.querySelector(".stake-cell").textContent = formatMoney(stake);
      });

      bookResult.textContent = formatPercent(bookPercentage);
      returnResult.textContent = formatMoney(equalReturn);
      profitResult.textContent = formatMoney(profit);
      profitResult.className = profit >= 0 ? "positive" : "negative";

      if (bookPercentage < 100) {
        marginResult.textContent = `${margin.toFixed(2)}% underround`;
        marginResult.className = "positive";
        resultNote.textContent = `This creates an underround. Splitting ${formatMoney(totalStake)} across all outcomes would return about ${formatMoney(equalReturn)}, giving an estimated profit of ${formatMoney(profit)}.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note";
      } else if (bookPercentage > 100) {
        marginResult.textContent = `${margin.toFixed(2)}% overround`;
        marginResult.className = "negative";
        resultNote.textContent = `This does not create an arbitrage. The market is ${formatPercent(bookPercentage)}, so covering all outcomes would produce an estimated loss of ${formatMoney(Math.abs(profit))}.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note warning";
      } else {
        marginResult.textContent = "0.00% fair book";
        marginResult.className = "";
        resultNote.textContent = `This is close to a fair book before practical issues such as commission, limits and odds movement.`;
        resultNote.className = "result-note";
      }
    }

    function renderRows(rows) {
      tableBody.innerHTML = "";
      rows.forEach((row) => tableBody.appendChild(createRow(row.name, row.odds)));
      calculateArbitrage();
    }

    tableBody.addEventListener("input", calculateArbitrage);

    tableBody.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
      if (!event.target.classList.contains("remove-row")) return;

      const rows = tableBody.querySelectorAll("tr");

      if (rows.length <= 2) {
        resultNote.textContent = "An arbitrage calculation needs at least two outcomes.";
        resultNote.className = "result-note error";
        return;
      }

      event.target.closest("tr").remove();
      calculateArbitrage();
    });

    totalStakeInput.addEventListener("input", calculateArbitrage);

    addButton.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const nextNumber = tableBody.querySelectorAll("tr").length + 1;
      tableBody.appendChild(createRow(`Outcome ${nextNumber}`, ""));
      calculateArbitrage();
    });

    resetButton.addEventListener("click", () => {
      totalStakeInput.value = "100";
      renderRows(exampleRows);
    });

    calculateArbitrage();
  </script>
</MainLayout>
